"{\"uid\": \"limerickleader.ie-news-national-news-1578408-daniel-wiffen-confirms-river-seine-made-him-sick-at-olympics.html\", \"text\": \"Limerick Live  https://www.limerickleader.ie/section/1195/advertise-with-us  Search  02 Dec 2025  Bringing you live local breaking news, sport, politics, weather & more in Limerick and County Limerick  All the latest breaking local news from Limerick and County Limerick  Keep up to date with the latest sports news  Ryder Cup  Read all the latest Irish news and updates from around Ireland  Find whats happening in and around Limerick and County Limerick  Life Magazines  Enjoy our award winning photos and picture galleries taken in Limerick and County Limerick  Catch up on all the latest business news in Limerick and County Limerick  Read about the latest properties available in Limerick and County Limerick  Enjoy our latest and up to date motoring review and news in Limerick and County Limerick  Limerick and County Limerick Met Eireann Weather Forecast  Recent death notices and obituaries from Limerick and County Limerick  Please allow ads as they help fund our trusted local news content.  Kindly addusto your ad blocker whitelist.  If you want further access to Ireland's best local journalism, consider contributing and/or subscribing to our free daily Newsletter .  Support our mission and join our community now.  To continue reading this article, you can subscribe for as little as \\u20ac0.50 per week which will also give you access to all of our premium content and archived articles!  Alternatively, you can pay \\u20ac0.50 per article, capped at \\u20ac1 per day.  Thank you for supporting Ireland's best local journalism!  Reporter:  Reporter  13 Aug 2024 2:04 PM  Olympic hero Daniel Wiffen has spoken up about why he pulled out of carrying the Irish flag on the Paris Olympics closing ceremony.  The 23-year-old confirmed that he got sick over the past couple of days after swimming in the River Seine.  \\\"I am OK, I was a bit ill for the past couple of days from the River Seine, but I am starting to recover now and it's gone through my system, so I am looking forward to this,\\\" he told Cool FM during Team Ireland homecoming celebration on Monday.  READ MORE:\\u00a0Popular Irish castle and four star hotel to feature on new TV show in the UK  Ahead of the ceremony, Wiffen posted on X, formerly known as Twitter: \\\"Thanks everyone who reached out, I am incredibly disappointed to miss out on the opportunity to be flag bearer last night. Yesterday, I rushed to hospital as I was very unwell with a bug that I am being treated for, and am feeling better now. I hope everyone enjoys the evening and I hope to be well enough to seeing everyone when we get home.\\\"  Related topics:  national news  4  To continue reading this article,please subscribe and support local journalism!  Subscribing will allow you access to all of our premium content and archived articles.  To continue reading this article for FREE,please kindly register and/or log in.  Registration is absolutely 100% FREE and will help us personalise your experience on our sites.  You can also sign up to our carefully curated newsletter(s) to keep up to date with your latest local news!  Most Popular  Crime and Courts  The scene of the crash on Upper William Street  Crime and Courts  Pictures & Videos  Hurling  Crime and Courts  Sponsored Content  Sponsored Content  Sponsored  Sponsored Content  With dark evenings closing in, it's the perfect time to curl up with a hot chocolate, a cosy blanket, and the November/December edition of Limerick Life  Sponsored Content  From sunlight to sustainability: The journey starts with Future Power  Sponsored Content  Multimedia  Pictures & Videos  Limerick Sport  Pictures & Videos  Pictures & Videos  Limerick Sport  Subscribe or register today to discover more from DonegalLive.ie  Buy the e-paper of the Donegal Democrat, Donegal People's Press, Donegal Post and Inish Times here for instant access to Donega